<p><em>14.	WORKING WITH LAYERS </em></p>

<p>

<b>LAYERS</b><br>
In PageMaker there is layers. 
This allows you to organize your document into a series  of  overlapping layers, controlling their stack order, 
appearance and locking preferences.
</p><p>
  <code>Showing Layer Palette</code><br>
  1. Click Window menu > Show layers...
 </p><p> 
<code>To create a new layer,</code> follow these steps:<br>
1. Select New Layer from the Layer palette menu.<br>

2. Choose any of the following options:<br>
<ul>
  <li>Type a name of the layer in the Name text box. 
By default layers are named according to the order in which they were created. </li>
  <li>Select a color from the Selection Color pop-up menu to indicate selected objects in that layer.</li>
  <li>Select or deselect the Show option to display or hide the layer.</li>
  <li>Select or deselect the Lock option to lock or unlock objects on the layer.</li>
</ul>

3. Click OK.

